    <item>
      <title>Mint Flavoured Markdown</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/mfm/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/mfm/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;        &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/media/mfm-banner.webp&#34; alt=&#34;The Mint Flavoured Markdown logo, a capital &amp;#39;M&amp;#39; covered in minty vegetation and adjacent to an arrow pointing down. Designed by Imagen 4, edited by Ethan Marks&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When I started designing and prototyping my &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/personalwebsite&#34;&gt;personal website&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, I was very much inspired by &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://leanrada.com/notes/vanilla-web-rewrite/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;this blog post&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; by &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://leanrada.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Lean Rada&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;. Basically, it advocates for authoring blog content in pure &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;HTML&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, rather than using a &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_site_generator&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;static site generator&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; like &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jekyll_%28software%29&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; that converts &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Markdown&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; into HTML.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This made a lot of sense to me, as I really didn&amp;rsquo;t want to have to learn Jekyll (in fact, I wanted to &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strange_Case_of_Dr_Jekyll_and_Mr_Hyde&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Hyde&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; from it entirely). So for a couple months, I authored each and every blog post in pure HTML.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Personal Website</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/personalwebsite/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 14 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/personalwebsite/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;My personal website is my home on the web.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;        &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/index.html&#34; alt=&#34;homepage&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I made this site because I want to have an online presence, but I don&amp;rsquo;t want to use social media (e.g. &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.instagram.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;), nor do I want to use someone else&amp;rsquo;s premade blogging platform (e.g. &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.blogger.com&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Blogger&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tumblr.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Tumblr&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://wordpress.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Wordpress&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My solution was to code an entire site from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tech&#34;&gt;Tech&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This site is completely static and is written entirely in pure vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It uses a few unavoidable premade libraries and services, but it&amp;rsquo;s completely free from major frameworks (e.g. &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://react.dev/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;React&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://vuejs.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Vue.js&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;, &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://angular.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Angular&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
